```json
{
  "application": "IOR",
  "details": {
    "resource": "Ookami-Cray",
    "environment": {
      "modules": [
        "slurm",
        "cray-mvapich2_nogpu_svealpha/2.3.4",
        "cray-hdf5-parallel/1.12.0.2"
      ],
      "variables": {
        "AKRR_NODES": "1",
        "AKRR_CORES": "48",
        "AKRR_CORES_PER_NODE": "48",
        "AKRR_NETWORK_SCRATCH": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch",
        "AKRR_LOCAL_SCRATCH": "/tmp",
        "AKRR_TASK_WORKDIR": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/akrr_data/Ookami-Cray/ior/2020.12.02.04.08.23.105788",
        "AKRR_APPKER_DIR": "/lustre/home/xdmod/appker/Ookami",
        "AKRR_AKRR_DIR": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/akrr_data/Ookami-Cray",
        "AKRR_APPKER_NAME": "ior",
        "AKRR_RESOURCE_NAME": "Ookami-Cray",
        "AKRR_TIMESTAMP": "2020.12.02.04.08.23.105788",
        "AKRR_APP_STDOUT_FILE": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/akrr_data/Ookami-Cray/ior/2020.12.02.04.08.23.105788/appstdout",
        "AKRR_APPKERNEL_INPUT": "/lustre/home/xdmod/appker/Ookami/inputs",
        "AKRR_APPKERNEL_EXECUTABLE": "/lustre/home/xdmod/appker/Ookami/execs/ior",
        "AKRR_NODELIST": "`srun -l --ntasks-per-node=$AKRR_CORES_PER_NODE -n $AKRR_CORES hostname -s|sort -n| awk '{printf "%s ",$2}' `",
        "AKRR_TMP_WORKDIR": "`mktemp -d /lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/ior.XXXXXXXXX`",
        "EXE": "$AKRR_APPKER_DIR/execs/ior/3.3.0rc1_cray_mvapich/bin/ior",
        "RUNMPI": "srun -n $AKRR_CORES -N $AKRR_NODES -r 0",
        "RUNMPI_OFFSET": "srun -N $AKRR_NODES -n $AKRR_CORES -r 1",
        "COMMON_TEST_PARAM": "-b 200m -t 20m",
        "COMMON_OPTIONS": "-vv",
        "CACHING_BYPASS": "-Z",
        "TESTS_LIST": "[-a POSIX $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_1\n-a POSIX -F $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_N\n-a MPIIO $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_1\n-a MPIIO -c $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_1\n-a MPIIO -F $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_N\n-a HDF5 $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_1\n-a HDF5 -c $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_1\n-a HDF5 -F $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION_N_to_N]",
        "COMMON_PARAM": "$COMMON_OPTIONS $RESOURCE_SPECIFIC_OPTION $CACHING_BYPASS $COMMON_TEST_PARAM"
      }
    },
    "slurm_options": {
      "partition": "short",
      "qos": "short",
      "nodes": "2",
      "ntasks_per_node": "48",
      "time": "03:00:00",
      "output": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/akrr_data/Ookami-Cray/ior/2020.12.02.04.08.23.105788/stdout",
      "error": "/lustre/home/xdmod/scratch/akrr_data/Ookami-Cray/ior/2020.12.02.04.08.23.105788/stderr",
      "exclusive": true
    }
  }
}
```

**Explanation:**

* **Application:** The script is running the IOR (I/O Rate) benchmark.
* **Details:**
    * **Resource:** The benchmark is executed on the "Ookami-Cray" supercomputer.
    * **Environment:**
        * **Modules:** The script loads the `slurm`, `cray-mvapich2_nogpu_svealpha/2.3.4`, and `cray-hdf5-parallel/1.12.0.2` modules.
        * **Variables:** Various environment variables are set, including paths to scratch directories, application kernels, working directories, output files, and other configuration settings.
    * **SLURM Options:** The script uses SLURM (Simple Linux Utility for Resource Management) to submit the job. It specifies the partition, QoS level, number of nodes, tasks per node, time limit, output file, error file, and requests exclusive access to the resources.
